{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01NotM8FTefjHLqzPbN6QPfJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is complete and verified.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** After the \"permissions change,\" `reporting-user` had been granted a custom role `rawRead` that allowed `find` on **`appdb.raw`** (the ingestion data that must stay private) and had **no** access to `appdb.reports` — so dashboards (which read `appdb.reports`) failed, while the sensitive `raw` collection was improperly exposed.\n\n**Fix (least privilege):**\n1. Created a minimal custom role `reportsRead` on `appdb` granting only `find` on `appdb.reports`.\n2. Granted `reportsRead` to `reporting-user` and revoked `rawRead`.\n3. Resynced `reporting-user`'s password to match the `reporting-user-password` Secret (its DB password was out of sync, blocking authentication entirely).\n\n**Verification** (authenticating as `reporting-user` with the Secret's password, `authSource=admin`):\n- `appdb.reports` → readable (4 docs) ✅\n- `appdb.raw` → **Unauthorized** ✅\n\nNo operators/CRDs used; admin password and replica set were left untouched."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":570,"cache_read_input_tokens":34972,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":570},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82267a20-6d0f-41da-ae3e-1b1a2b1d8878","uuid":"1a89ab50-9fe6-448e-b085-cdf0df30e386","request_id":"req_011CcB1zPxiRdAGHoKS2vfWH"}
